\section{Overview of Manchester's emissions}

Table~\ref{table:summary_all} puts Manchester's current \COO\ emissions in
context. The emissions shown in the table are given on an an end-user
basis. That is, the emissions from the production of certain forms of energy
(mainly electricity) are allocated to the user of that energy, rather than the
producer.
%
\begin{table}[ht]
<<label = summary_all, echo = FALSE>>=
format(dcast(cities.co2, city ~ yr, function(x) {0.001 * sum(x)}, value.var =
             "CO2"), digits = 3)
@ 
\caption{Total \COO\ emissions (in \si{Mt.\COO}) from selected cities on an
  end-user basis. Figures are from DECC's regional energy
  statistics~\cite{decc-regional-emissions}.}
\label{table:summary_all}
\end{table}
%
