Greater Manchester is composed of ten boroughs, the emissions of which are
broken out by sector in table~\ref{table:borough-emissions}. 
\begin{table}[ht]
<<label = manchester_co2, echo = FALSE>>=
format(dcast(subset(cities.co2, city == "Manchester" & yr == 2010),
             la_name ~ sector0,
             sum, 
             value.var = "CO2", margins = TRUE), big.mark = ",", digits = 1)
@ 
\caption{\label{table:borough-emissions} Emissions from the ten boroughs. Note
  that the high-level sectors shown here are not identical to those in the data as
  published by DECC: Railways have been included within Transport, Large
 Industrial The abbreviated sectors are ``Industrial and Commercial''
  and ``Large Industrial Installations''.}
\end{table}


